did.abstract: Founded by Rufus S. Lusk, Sr.(d. 1971), Rufus S. Lusk & Son, Inc. was the leader in the Mid-Atlantic region for providing the most accurate and reliable real estate sales, ownership, and mortgage information. For nearly 70 year, the Rufus S. Lusk & Son company published real estate information products which made a significant contribution to the Washington area community. Within the collection much of the collection is related to the work of Lusk & Son, but there are also materials related to other activities for Rufus S. Lusk including the Washington Taxpayers' Association and the Washington Taxpayers' Protective Association, and the Gourmet Society Dinner Club. The material dates from the 1930s through 1994. The material in Series 3 relates to The Tri-State Commission and the Washington Metropolitan Transportation Authority (METRO). These records appear to all come from the records of Jerome M. Alper.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Collection remains in original order, but folder titles were organized within the finding aid and three series were created for ease of browsing the finding aid: Business records, Civic and personal records, and Transportation

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Founded by Rufus S. Lusk, Sr.(d. 1971), Rufus S. Lusk & Son, Inc. was the leader in the Mid-Atlantic region for providing the most accurate and reliable real estate sales, ownership, and mortgage information. For nearly 70 year, the Rufus S. Lusk & Son company published real estate information products which made a significant contribution to the Washington area community. While the Lusk company primarily served the real estate and financial communities through the dissemination of its information, homeowners and others interested in real estate trends used Lusk publications to keep abreast of developments. In 1997, the company was sold. In addition to his work in the real estate industry Rufus Lusk, Sr. was also involved in other aspects of Washington DC business and social society. He founded the Gourmet Dinner Society and the Washington Taxpayers' Association and served as a member of the Greater Washington Board of Trade.

The District of Columbia Real Estate Directory provides data about all realty in Washington. The Lusk company also produced three weekly publications including Real Estate Guides. This service provided records transfers of property and real estate mortgages.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The material in this collection includes business records, publications, correspondence, financial reports, memorandum, and photographs. Much of this material is related to the work of Lusk & Son, but there are also materials related to other activities for Rufus S. Lusk including the Washington Taxpayers' Association and Washington Taxpayers' Protective Association, and the Gourmet Society Dinner Club. The material dates from the 1930s through 1994. The material in Series 3 relates to The Tri-State Commission and the Washington Metropolitan Transporation Authority (METRO). These records appear to all come from the records of Jerome M. Alper.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Gift of Rufus Speake Lusk, III, September 20, 1996
